<item>
            <title>[LU-14881] SUSE 15 SP3 build fails with redefined tcp_sock_set_* functions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14881</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux commits:  &lt;br/&gt;
  v5.7-rc6-2504-gddd061b8daed&lt;br/&gt;
  tcp: add tcp_sock_set_quickack&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  v5.7-rc6-2508-gd41ecaac903c&lt;br/&gt;
  tcp: add tcp_sock_set_keepintvl&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  v5.7-rc6-2509-g480aeb9639d6&lt;br/&gt;
  tcp: add tcp_sock_set_keepcnt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Introduced a series of helper functions that may be&lt;br/&gt;
back ported individually.&lt;br/&gt;
In this case it breaks building SUSE 15 SP3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add the some configure treatment for these as was done previously for &lt;br/&gt;
  tcp_sock_set_nodelay() and tcp_sock_set_keepidle()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
